DEFINITIONS AND RESPONSIBILITIES

This section provides clear definitions of key terms used within this SOP and outlines the roles and
responsibilities of personnel involved in the data backup and recovery process. Understanding
these definitions and responsibilities ensures all parties are aligned and aware of their duties.

DEFINITIONS

Backup

RESPONSIBILITIES

IT Specialist

The process of creating a copy of data to
protect it against loss or corruption.

Recovery

The process of restoring data from a backup
after data loss or corruption.

Incremental Backup

A backup that captures only the changes made
since the last backup.

Full Backup

A complete copy of all data.

Disaster Recovery Plan (DRP)

A documented process or set of procedures to
recover and protect a business IT infrastructure
in the event of a disaster.

Retention Period

The duration for which backup data is kept
before it is deleted or overwritten.

Responsible for performing regular backups,
monitoring backup processes, and initiating
recovery procedures when necessary.

Data Owner

Responsible for ensuring that the data under
their management is classified correctly, backed
up according to the prescribed schedule, and
accessible for recovery operations. They also
coordinate with the IT department to address
any issues or special requirements related to
data backup and recovery.

IT Manager

Ensures compliance with the backup schedule,
reviews backup logs, and oversees recovery
testing.

Chief Information Officer (CIO)

Approves backup and recovery policies, and
ensures adequate resources are allocated for
backup infrastructure and processes.

